    #samples-tile.ribbon
      .carousel
        h2 Samples
        .sample-element
          img(src='librarySketches/library__0gates.png', alt="A LogiJS example sketch showing the three basic logic gates")
          .sample-description
            h3 Basic Gates 
            a.open_link(href="/editor?sketch=library__0gates", rel="nofollow") <i class="fa fa-play"></i> OPEN
            p.clear This sketch demonstrates the three basic logic gates, AND, OR and XOR. It also shows the usage of input and output elements. Logic gates are the fundamentals of every logic circuit.
        .sample-element
          img(src='librarySketches/library__14BitCounter.png', alt="A LogiJS example sketch showing a four bit counter")
          .sample-description
            h3 4-Bit Counter
            a.open_link(href="/editor?sketch=library__14BitCounter", rel="nofollow") <i class="fa fa-play"></i> OPEN
            p.clear This sketch implements a simple counter made using D gates. It is connected to a clock, permanently increasing the binary output value. When the value passes the biggest possible value, the counter restarts from zero.
        .sample-element
          img(src='librarySketches/library__2traffic.png', alt="A LogiJS example sketch showing a traffic light simulation")
          .sample-description
            h3 Traffic Lights
            a.open_link(href="/editor?sketch=library__2traffic", rel="nofollow") <i class="fa fa-play"></i> OPEN
            p.clear This sketch simulates traffic lights using a counter and a diode matrix. There is a light for road traffic and one for crossing pedestrians.
