    #features-tile.ribbon
      .carousel
        h2 Features
        .feature-element
          p.feature-icon <i class="fa fa-cloud-upload-alt fa-4x"></i>
          h3 Save Your Sketches Online
          p <a href="/signup">Register for a free user account</a> that allows you to manage your circuits online! After registration, you get access to a dashboard where you can save your circuits. On top of that, you may import your circuits into other circuits as custom modules.
        .feature-element
          p.feature-icon <i class="fa fa-drafting-compass fa-4x"></i>
          h3 Create Your Own Elements
          p Many circuits contain the same logic structures multiple times. In LogiJS, you can build these structures in separate sketches to load them into your projects. To use this feature, please <a href="/signup">register for a free account</a>. Feel free to build a library of modules for use in your projects! Have fun!
        .feature-element
          p.feature-icon <i class="fa fa-graduation-cap fa-4x"></i>
          h3 Focused On Education
          p LogiJS was built with education in mind. Its clear and distraction free design makes it a powerful tool for teaching the fundamentals of logic circuits. We believe that great software can spark interest and help to give students a deep understanding of electrical engineering basics.
    
    #about-tile.sidebar
      h2 What is LogiJS?
      img(src='images/sample_sketch_1.png', alt="A LogiJS example sketch showing a part of a counter")
      p
        | LogiJS is an open source logic circuit simulator. Logic circuits are everywhere these days and therefore taught at universities worldwide. 
      p
        | Our goal is to offer a software 
        | that isn't only free for everybody, but also encourages students to get creative with logic circuits and develop a deep understanding of the basic concepts. Our goal is not to
        | build a software for production use or for learning advanced techniques. Instead, we focuse on simplicity to create an experimenting playground free of distractions and frustrations.
      p
        | Please note that LogiJS is currently in active development. Changes may come rapidly and unanounced. Also, we can't guarantee for possible data loss or damage done trough use of our software.
      p
        | If you would like to learn more about the technical side of LogiJS or are interested in supporting us, please visit our project on <a href="https://www.github.com/SimonBuxx/LogiJS">GitHub</a>.
      .clear
    #upcoming-tile.sidebar
      h2 Planned Features
      ul
        img(src='images/sample_sketch_2.png', alt="A LogiJS example sketch showing a part of a counter")
        li First things first, we will finally complete the selection feature so that you can move, copy and delete sketch parts.
        li We'd like to have a showroom for user-built circuits, where you can view other user's circuits and edit them as copies in your own dashboards. For this, we need to find a way to handle sketch dependencies (custom elements used in the sketch).
        li VHDL and Verilog are the most common hardware description languages. We want to support export to at least one of them. This is useful for exporting circuits to FPGAs and other applications.
        li Users should be able to edit sketches with multiple users at the same time. Users should also get the possibility to share sketches via unique links.
        li If you have feature suggestions or want to report problems or bugs, please feel free to open an issue in our <a href="https://www.github.com/SimonBuxx/LogiJS">GitHub</a>.
      .clear
